# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your actual values.
**NEVER commit the `.env` file to version control!**

## Development Environment
DB_PORT_DEV=3306
DB_HOST_DEV=localhost
DB_NAME_DEV=horarios
DB_USER_DEV=root
DB_PASSWORD_DEV=

## QA Environment
DB_PORT_QA=3306
DB_HOST_QA=qa-db.example.com
DB_NAME_QA=horarios_qa
DB_USER_QA=your_qa_username
DB_PASSWORD_QA=your_qa_password

## Staging Environment
DB_PORT_STAGING=3306
DB_HOST_STAGING=staging-db.example.com
DB_NAME_STAGING=horarios_staging
DB_USER_STAGING=your_staging_username
DB_PASSWORD_STAGING=your_staging_password

## Production Environment
DB_PORT_PROD=3306
DB_HOST_PROD=prod-db.example.com
DB_NAME_PROD=horarios_prod
DB_USER_PROD=your_prod_username
DB_PASSWORD_PROD=your_prod_password

## Liquibase Configuration
LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_URL=jdbc:mysql://${DB_HOST_DEV}:${DB_PORT_DEV}/${DB_NAME_DEV}
LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_USERNAME=${DB_USER_DEV}
LIQUIBASE_COMMAND_PASSWORD=${DB_PASSWORD_DEV}